President Donald J. Trump has sent warm wishes to Sikh Americans and Sikhs worldwide as they celebrate the birth anniversary of Guru Nanak Devji, the founder of Sikhism. He acknowledges the Sikh community for embodying values such as peace, tolerance, compassion, and service, which are shared by all Americans. President Trump also recognizes the significant contributions made by Sikh Americans to the nation, both in military and public service, for over a century.